Package oracle.kubernetes.operator.helpers

Class ResponseStep<T>

java.lang.Object
oracle.kubernetes.operator.work.Step
oracle.kubernetes.operator.helpers.ResponseStep<T>
Type Parameters:
T - Response type
Direct Known Subclasses:
DefaultResponseStep
public abstract class ResponseStep<T>
extends Step
Step to receive response of Kubernetes API server call.

Most implementations will only need to implement onSuccess(Packet, CallResponse).

      public NextAction onFailure​(Packet packet, CallResponse<T> callResponse)

    • onFailure

      public NextAction onFailure​(Step conflictStep, Packet packet, CallResponse<T> callResponse)
      Callback for API server call failure. The ApiException and HTTP status code and response headers are provided; however, these will be null or 0 when the client simply timed-out.

      The default implementation tests if the request could be retried and, if not, ends fiber processing.

      Parameters:
      conflictStep - Conflict step
      packet - Packet
      callResponse - the result of the call
      Returns:
      Next action for fiber processing, which may be a retry
